 on Firefox/Firebug, select CSS as selector

    input[id='displayd-text']

 the above CSS locator will highlight the "Hide/SHow Example" text box

 Now the shortcut is to use the syntax on finding ID - "#" - ID

    #displayed-text

 The above locator also shows the same



If there are multiple nodes with the same ID as 'displayed-text' then specifically add the tag:

    input#displayed-text

  the above shortens the search


input[id=displayed-text]
#displayed-text
